But as long as you're picking apart my post (as if I have a chart that keeps track of what drops what), I'm going to respond; I don't care what you raiders do. In no post have I stated that I dislike raiding guilds or the people in them. This is all I was attempting to express:<br>
<br>
• I don't think I should be obligated to worship <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> any</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> guild, or player, for that matter, for whatever they accomplish in this game. Much like Graves said, it's all just pixels. Does raiding PoF mean that you're a skilled player? Certainly. Does it mean that you're a better person? No. You've isolated yourself from family and friends for yet another eight hours, and chances are you didn't get anything from it.<br>
<br>
• I think raids are all about loot. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> In my opinion</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (and I stress that because everyone is taking me too seriously), first-time encounters are the only thing that isn't directly involved with someone getting something. Granted, by that definition, I was wrong in my response to your Bristlebane thread. I did post in another thread, somewhere, that I didn't know it was a server first.<br>
